snippet: Rapper Torence "Lil Boosie" Hatch was ordered Thursday to perform 100 hours of community service in New Orleans as part of his four-year probation term stemming from a 2009 guilty plea to a marijuana possession charge....

headline.print_headline: Lil Boosie's Probation Includes Community Service
headline.main: Lil Boosie's Probation Includes Community Service

lead_paragraph: Rapper Torence "Lil Boosie" Hatch was ordered Thursday to perform 100 hours of community service in New Orleans as part of his four-year probation term stemming from a 2009 guilty plea to a marijuana possession charge.
